,{"id":"fa338d9c-c007-5424-a185-d45d3cc97aaa","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"5d32b973-0a04-5d8c-b893-01ef9ed83901","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"90a0f50a-373e-5e79-b347-ef01e0b5414b","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"5677a363-6aaa-51f8-8718-070e5c7f6636","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"47be6692-bf87-5832-8dfe-c5be55c71004","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"ab73eb28-31fa-545f-939a-53d4e82c18b0","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"91e54862-93aa-5c58-820e-b47769d73d34","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"b8f01d98-81c5-5a1a-9159-64f8b79ff85c","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"21f82196-e0cc-579f-a4aa-260db78f847d","slug":"prescribing-information","fullItemName":"Prescribing information"},"subChapters":[{"id":"05da8f3a-9864-5ae2-b090-37eae05a8f94","slug":"cautions-contraindications","fullItemName":"Cautions and contraindications","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 89e629e8-e747-4343-965d-a6d300eb7f06 --><h3>What are the cautions and contraindications associated with chlorhexidine mouthwash?</h3><!-- end field 89e629e8-e747-4343-965d-a6d300eb7f06 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 48856d22-89ae-4c6f-8b04-a6d300eb7cca --><!-- begin field ad6b1657-5eb7-45cc-baad-a6d300eb7f06 --><ul><li>Do not prescribe chlorhexidine to people who have previously experienced a hypersensitivity reaction to it or its excipients.</li></ul><p>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/gingivitis-periodontitis/references/\">ABPI Medicines Compendium, 2016b</a>] </p><!-- end field ad6b1657-5eb7-45cc-baad-a6d300eb7f06 --><!-- end item 48856d22-89ae-4c6f-8b04-a6d300eb7cca -->","subChapters":[]},{"id":"2ac42d5e-ee8c-53c7-ac68-8bd64fb83b13","slug":"adverse-effects","fullItemName":"Adverse effects","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 6ab20f1d-3f4e-46df-83b9-a6d300eb924f --><h3>What are the adverse effects of chlorhexidine?</h3><!-- end field 6ab20f1d-3f4e-46df-83b9-a6d300eb924f -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 959460ce-1fa0-479b-ada1-a6d300eb9033 --><!-- begin field 01f00c03-90dd-456c-a1e4-a6d300eb924f --><ul><li>Adverse effects reported with the use of chlorhexidine 2% mouthwash include:<ul><li>Superficial discolouration of the tongue and/or teeth (not permanent).<ul><li>Advise the person to reduce their tea, coffee and red wine intake.</li><li>Note that chlorhexidine gluconate may not be compatible with some ingredients in toothpaste. Advise the person to leave a minimum of 30 minutes between using mouthwash and toothpaste. The mouth should be rinsed well with water between using toothpaste and mouthwashes containing chlorhexidine.</li><li>Some people will require treatment by a dentist to remove staining.</li></ul></li><li>Transient altered taste and burning sensation of the tongue - usually improves with continued use.</li><li>Mucosal irritation — if oral desquamation occurs, advise dilution of mouthwash with an equal volume of water before use.</li><li>Rarely, parotid gland swelling, irritative skin reactions, and allergic reactions (including anaphylaxis).</li></ul></li></ul><p>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/gingivitis-periodontitis/references/\">ABPI Medicines Compendium, 2016b</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/gingivitis-periodontitis/references/\">BNF 72, 2016</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/gingivitis-periodontitis/references/\">Scottish Dental Clinical Effectiveness Programme, 2016</a>]</p><!-- end field 01f00c03-90dd-456c-a1e4-a6d300eb924f --><!-- end item 959460ce-1fa0-479b-ada1-a6d300eb9033 -->","subChapters":[]},{"id":"fb627dd8-7b5f-5f6e-92c6-42f2f1234838","slug":"drug-interactions","fullItemName":"Drug interactions","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 2f0011ff-eb2e-4b40-a802-a6d300ebe37b --><h3>What are the important interactions with chlorhexidine mouthwash?</h3><!-- end field 2f0011ff-eb2e-4b40-a802-a6d300ebe37b -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 97385d77-ff42-4388-9835-a6d300ebe12f --><!-- begin field 4fd3e87f-dfb5-4b2d-a9c4-a6d300ebe37b --><ul><li>Chlorhexidine is incompatible with anionic agents.</li></ul><p>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/gingivitis-periodontitis/references/\">ABPI Medicines Compendium, 2016b</a>] </p><!-- end field 4fd3e87f-dfb5-4b2d-a9c4-a6d300ebe37b --><!-- end item 97385d77-ff42-4388-9835-a6d300ebe12f -->","subChapters":[]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}